foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: * In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, NOAA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2012 as “166.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “15” requests is due to requests fulfilled in FY2012, but not documented until FY 2013. The correct number is “151.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2012 for NOAA has been amended to “151” in the FY2013 Annual FOIA Report.

**In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, OIG reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2012 as “3.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “3” requests is due to requests pending which were not counted as pending in FY2012.

*** In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests pending at the end of FY2012 was reported as “340.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2013 for NOAA and OIG (see footnotes above), the agency overall number of requests pending as of the start of FY2013 has been amended to “328.”

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: *In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, International Trade Administration (ITA) reported “2” consultations pending. One of the ITA reported consultation on last year’s report was actually a referral. Therefore, the number of consultations pending as of the start of FY2013 for ITA has been amended to “1” in the FY2013 Annual FOIA Report.

** In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of consultations pending at the end of FY2012 was reported as “5.” Due to the amendment in the number of consultations pending as of the start of FY2013 for ITA (see footnote above), the agency overall number of consultations pending as of the start of FY2013 has been amended to “4.”

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: * In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, NOAA reported the number of requests processed during the Fiscal Year as “465.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “15” requests is due to requests fulfilled in FY2012, but not documented until FY2013. Therefore, the number of requests processed as of the end of FY2012 for NOAA was actually “480.”

** In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests processed during the Fiscal Year as “1701.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests processed for NOAA in FY2012 (see footnote above), the agency overall number of requests processed during FY2012 for the agency overall was actually “1716.”

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: *In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, NOAA reported the number of requests backlogged at the end of FY 2011 as “128.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “15” requests is due to requests fulfilled in FY 2012, but not documented until FY2013. Therefore, the number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2012 for NOAA was actually “113.”

** In the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests backlogged at the end of FY2012 was reported as “227.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2012 for NOAA (see footnote above), the agency overall number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2012 for the agency overall was actually “212.”
